{
  "page_type": "function",
  "name": "linResetMasterNode",
  "category": "LIN",
  "title": "linResetMasterNode",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/LIN/Functions/CAPLfunctionLINResetMasterNode.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "long linResetMasterNode();"
  ],
  "description": [
    "Calling this function reverses the effect of linSetMasterNode. Sending LIN headers (by calling linTransmitHeader or similar functions) is no longer restricted to the currently assigned LIN master node. If a node is assigned as LDF master node, the LIN scheduler will be reset to its state before linSetMasterNode was called."
  ],
  "parameters": [],
  "return": "Node ID of the previous master node. If the return value is 0 (zero), the function failed, or there was no previous LIN master node.",
